{"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular"},"kind":"article","topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide"],"title":"Guides","anchor":"Guides"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],"title":"Guides","anchor":"Guides"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"],["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Spooktacular runs macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework. You interact with it through the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"GUI app or the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"text":" CLI — both backed by the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"},{"text":" library. A Kubernetes operator is planned for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a future release.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]}]},{"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI","level":3,"text":"Creating a VM with the CLI","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook clone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"instant copies.","type":"text"}]}]},{"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI","level":3,"text":"Creating a VM with the GUI","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Open Spooktacular.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Click the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"+"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" button or press ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cmd+N"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Click ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"into a new VM bundle.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Managing-VMs","level":3,"text":"Managing VMs","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"]},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CapacityCheck","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for details.","type":"text"}]}]},{"anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts","level":3,"text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ssh"},{"text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"progress. See ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProvisioningMode"},{"text":" for provisioning strategies and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"doc:Provisioning","type":"text"},{"text":" for detailed guidance.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup","level":3,"text":"EC2 Mac Setup","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment"},{"text":" for detailed EC2 Mac configuration.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A Kubernetes operator (MacOSVM CRD) is planned for a future","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"release. See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for the planned architecture.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/OpenClawGuide":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/openclawguide","title":"Running OpenClaw in Virtual Machines","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Run two isolated OpenClaw AI agent instances on a single Mac — each with its own workspace, channels, and API keys.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/CLIReference":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/clireference","title":"Using the spook Command-Line Interface","ki